SUMMARY:Greenwood Gardens Birder’s Walk
DESCRIPTION:Led by Dave Hall\, Associate Naturalist  \nImmerse yourself in nature on a guided walk through the garden with avian expert Dave Hall. Discover the diverse bird species that frequent Greenwood’s tranquil woodlands and the surrounding 2\,100 acres of protected parkland in South Mountain Reservation. Whether you are a seasoned birdwatcher or simply curious\, this is a unique opportunity to learn more about the feathered visitors that call this area home. Registration with Greenwood Gardens is required for this trip.  \nPlease click on the following link to register: Greenwood Gardens Birder’s Walk \nCost: $15  \nLocation: Greenwood Gardens\, 274 Old Short Hills Road\, Short Hills\, NJ 
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/greenwood-gardens-birders-walk-3/
LOCATION:Greenwood Gardens\, 274 Old Short Hills Rd\, Short Hills\, NJ\, 07078\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bird Walk,Birding,David Hall,Scherman Hoffman Wildlife Sanctuary
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Greenwood-Garden-Birders-Walk-04.2026.jpg
GEO:40.741972;-74.312061
