SUMMARY:Sandy Hook
DESCRIPTION:Early spring migration at “the hook.” If the winds are right\, we could have a good flight of hawks\, swallows\, and other migrants. Spring birding at the hook for migrants. The wide variety of habitats here ensures a good diversity of bird species from herons and egrets to shorebirds\, hawks\, and songbirds. Be prepared for a fair amount of walking over flat and sometimes sandy terrain. Meet at parking lot B by the bathrooms. Led by Linda Mack\, Carole Hughes\, Jonathan Klizas\, and Chris Daly. \nLocation: Meet at Parking Lot B\, about halfway down the lot by the bathrooms \nPRE-REGISTRATION REQUIRED \nCOST: $20 Members\, $25 Non-members \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/sandy-hook-14/
LOCATION:Sandy Hook – Lot B\, Hartshorne Drive\, Sandy Hook\, NJ\, 07732\, United States
CATEGORIES:All Things Birds,Bird Walk,Birding
